cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the use of machine learning models and techniques to improve the robustness of deep learning networks against adversarial attacks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper focuses on the security aspect of machine learning and proposes solutions to protect against adversarial attacks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed solutions on image datasets such as MNIST, CIFAR10, CIFAR100, and ImageNet. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence techniques to improve the robustness of deep learning networks against adversarial attacks. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper discusses the use of binary neural networks and related variants, which fall under the category of neural computing.
